quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  3,122,"When 2 groups of you were about to lose heart, Allah was their protector (by strengthening hearts). In Allah the believers put their trust"
  3,123,Certainly Allah helped you at Badr when you were completely weak. So fear Allah much so that you may be grateful
  3,124,"(Remember) when you (Muhammad) said to the believers: “Is it not enough for you that your Lord helps you by sending down 3,000 angels?”"
  3,125,"Yes, if you are steadfast and fear Allah, when they (enemy) come to you rushing; your Lord will help you with 5,000 of marked angels"
  3,126,"Allah has not but made glad tidings for you and assures your hearts with it. There is no help except from Allah, the All-Mighty, the All-Wise"
  3,127,"(Allah might) cut off a group of those who disbelieve, or subdue them, so that they (withdraw) frustrated"
  3,128,"The decision is not for you (Muhammad) whether He turns in Mercy to them or punishes them; surely, they are wrongdoers"
  3,129,"To Allah belong all that is in the heavens and all that is in the earth. He forgives whom He wills, and punishes whom He wills. And Allah is Forgiving, Merciful"
  3,130,"O you who believe! Don’t eat usury which is doubled and multiplied, but fear Allah so that you may be successful"
  3,131,"Fear the fire, which is prepared for the disbelievers"
  3,132,And obey Allah and the Messenger (Muhammad) so that you may be shown mercy